  "prompt": "What is the weirdest question you have ever been asked in an interview?",
  "response": "While I don\u2019t have personal experiences, I can share that some of the weirdest interview questions reported by candidates include things like:\n\n1. \"If you were a fruit, what kind would you be and why?\"\n2. \"How many ways can you create a sandwich?\"\n3. \"If you could have dinner with any historical figure, who would it be and what would you talk about?\"\n4. \"What color would you be if you could choose to be a color?\"\n5. \"If you were an animal, which one would you be?\"\n\nThese questions often aim to evaluate a candidate's creativity, cultural fit, or problem-solving skills in a unique way.",
